article.headline: Tenn.-Martin 99, Jacksonville St. 74
article.story: MARTIN, Tenn. -- Lester Hudson scored 27 points, leading four Tennessee-Martin players in double figures in a 99-74 rout of Jacksonville State on Thursday night. Delrico Lane added 13 points, while Benzor Simmons and Marquis Weddle chipped in with 12 apiece for the Skyhawks (17-6, 10-3 Ohio Valley Conference). Jeremy Bynum and Nick Murphy led the Gamecocks (11-13, 5-10) with 12 points apiece, and Stephen Hall added 11. The Skyhawks opened up an early lead, cruising to a 17-point halftime advantage. They didn't slow down much in the second, outscoring the Gamecocks 51-43 en route to victory. The Skyhawks won the rebounding battle, grabbing 37 to the Gamecocks' 28. Tennessee-Martin, which has won nine games in a row, swept the season series with the Gamecocks. Jacksonville State has lost two straight.
